---
title: Oven-Ready Soy-Glazed Chicken with Broccoli & Buttery Rice (trays included)
description: What do we love more than a delicious, home-cooked dinner? A delicious, home-cooked dinner that doesn’t require any prep OR dirtying multiple dishes! This week’s meal is just that. Sticky, savory-sweet chicken is served with buttery rice and sesame-studded broccoli—and it’s all ready in just 20 minutes. Now that’s a weeknight win!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/soy-glazed-chicken-2747dca8.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/oven-ready-soy-glazed-chicken-5f8dfe10d35147555b16012a-e8dbb1e7.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/oven-ready-soy-glazed-chicken-5f8dfe10d35147555b16012a
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: Asian
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 560 kcal
  fat: 16 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 66 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1070 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in 1 @oven-ready aluminum trays{2} (divide chicken
between 2 trays for 4 servings). Top chicken with @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}.

Roast on middle rack until cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Pour 1 TBSP water into remaining #tray{}. Add broccoli and drizzle with
@olive oil{1%teaspoon}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Sprinkle broccoli with half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} (save the rest for
serving). Cover tray with #foil{}. Roast on middle rack until tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

> TIP: If you like your broccoli a bit browned and crispy at the edges, remove
> foil from tray in the last 2-3 minutes of cooking.

Meanwhile, using your hands, massage @microwaveable jasmine rice{1} in package
to break up grains. Partially open package; place @butter{1%tablespoon} inside.
(For 4 servings, use 1 TBSP butter per package of rice.)

Microwave according to package directions. Carefully open package fully; season
rice with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Transfer to a #medium bowl{} and stir until
butter and seasonings are fully incorporated.

Divide rice between plates and top with chicken and glaze. Sprinkle with a
pinch of remaining sesame seeds and @korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste.
Serve with broccoli on the side.